DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,10,1);
$b1 = random(2,10,1);
$n1 = random(2,3,1);
$m1 = random(5,7,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Consider the function \( f(x) = \displaystyle \frac { $a1 }{ x^ {$n1} } - \frac { $b1 }{ x^ { $m1 }}  \). Let \( F(x) \) be the antiderivative of \( f(x) \) with \( F(1) = 0 \).  Find \(F(x)\).
$BR$BR\( F(x) =\) \{ans_rule(40) \}
END_TEXT

$n2= 1-$n1;
$a2= $a1/$n2;
$m2= 1-$m1;
$b2= -$b1/$m2;
$c = -($a1/(1-$n1)) + ($b1/(1-$m1));

$antideriv="$a2*x^($n2)+($b2)*x^($m2)+$c";

ANS(fun_cmp($antideriv, mode=>'antider'));


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOF'));
$SOL $BR

Recall that for a term of the form \( Ax^n \) the antiderivative is
just the term whose derivative is \( Ax^n \).  That is, 
\(\frac{A}{n+1}x^{n+1} + C \) where \( C \) is an unknown constant.
The antiderivative of a constant \( A \) is given by \( Ax \).  Finally, a
fraction such as \( \frac{A}{x^n} \) can be rewritten as \( Ax^{-n} \).
Applying these rules, we first rewrite the function as:
\[ 
  f(x) = {$a1}x^{-$n1} - {$b1}x^{-$m1}
\]
And then take the antiderivative to get: $BR$BR
\[ 
    F(x) = \frac{$a1}{$n2}x^{$n2} - \frac{$b1}{$m2}x^{$m2} + C  \] $BR
 \[   \ \ = \frac{!{$a2:%5.4f}}{x^{\{-$n2\}}} + \frac{!{$b2:%5.4f}}{x^{\{-$m2\}}} + C  \]

$BR$BR
Where \( C \) is an artibrary constant.  We are further more told that
\(F(1) = 0\) which we use to find the value of \( C \) as follows. $BR$BR
\[
  \begin{array}
    & F(1) = \frac{!{$a2:%5.4f}}{1^{\{-$n2\}}} + \frac{!{$b2:%5.4f}}{1^{\{-$m2\}}} + C &
    & 0    = !{$a2:%5.4f} + !{$b2:%5.4f} + C &
    & C    = !{$c:%5.4f}
  \end{align*}
\] $BR$BR
Therefore, the specific antiderivative is: $BR$BR
\[
  F(x) = \frac{!{$a2:%5.4f}}{x^{\{-$n2\}}} + \frac{!{$b2:%5.4f}}{x^{\{-$m2\}}} + !{$c:%5.4f}
\]

EOF


